WEBVTT

00:00:07.761 --> 00:00:11.079
If you ever find yourself 
gazing at falling snow,

00:00:11.079 --> 00:00:15.342
why not catch a few snowflakes 
on your glove and examine their shapes?

00:00:15.342 --> 00:00:17.438
You might notice 
that they look symmetrical,

00:00:17.438 --> 00:00:18.783
and if you look closely,

00:00:18.783 --> 00:00:21.124
you'll see they have six sides.

00:00:21.124 --> 00:00:24.217
You could say a snowflake 
is simply frozen water,

00:00:24.217 --> 00:00:26.873
but compare one 
with an ice cube from the freezer,

00:00:26.873 --> 00:00:29.802
and you'll realize 
they're very different things.

